        <section id="fs-id2282448" class="references" type="references">
            <title>References</title>
            <para id="import-auto-id2886692">Blumer, Herbert. 1969. “Collective Behavior.” Pp. 67–121 in <emphasis effect="italics">Principles of Sociology</emphasis>, edited by A.M. Lee. New York: Barnes and Noble.</para>
            <para id="import-auto-id2102970">LeBon, Gustave. 1960 [1895]. <emphasis effect="italics">The Crowd: A Study of the Popular Mind</emphasis>. New York: Viking Press.</para>
            <para id="import-auto-id2856540">Lofland, John. 1993. “Collective Behavior: The Elementary Forms.” Pp. 70–75 in <emphasis effect="italics">Collective Behavior and Social Movements</emphasis>, edited by Russel Curtis and Benigno Aguirre. Boston: Allyn and Bacon.</para>
            <para id="import-auto-id1449645">McPhail, Clark. 1991. <emphasis effect="italics">The Myth of the Madding Crowd</emphasis>. New York: Aldine de Gruyter.</para>
